The paper proposes a nonparametric causal discovery method based on observational data, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of kernel methods and reproducing kernel Hilbert spaces suggests a focus on machine learning and statistical learning theory, which are covered by cs.LG and cs.ST. The paper also mentions testing on real-world time series data, which suggests a focus on signal processing and information theory, covered by cs.IT. Finally, the use of decision rules and benchmark datasets suggests a focus on evaluation and comparison of methods, which is covered by cs.SI.
